.nh
.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-exec - Run a command in a running service container


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako exec SERVICE -- COMMAND [ARGS...] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run a command in the context of a deployed service.

.PP
By default the command runs inside a running replica (docker exec). With
--oneoff it runs in a fresh temporary container created from the service's
current image with the service's env, secrets, and network — useful for
framework tasks that should not share a serving process.

.PP
Without -i/-t the command is non-interactive: output streams back combined
(stdout+stderr) and there is no stdin. With -i stdin is forwarded over a
full-duplex stream; with -t the remote process additionally runs under a
pseudo-terminal that follows local window resizes — 'tako exec -it web -- sh'
is a usable shell. When local stdin is not a terminal, -t degrades to -i.

.PP
In the default text mode the tako process mirrors the remote command's exit
code; in machine modes the exit code is structured into the ExecResult
document instead. Interactive flags are rejected in machine modes: raw
terminal bytes are not events (control planes speak the documented ptystream
frame protocol directly).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for exec

.PP
\fB-i\fP, \fB--interactive\fP[=false]
	Forward stdin to the remote command

.PP
\fB--oneoff\fP[=false]
	Run in a fresh temporary container from the service's current image

.PP
\fB--replica\fP=0
	Running replica to attach to, 1-based (default: first)

.PP
\fB-s\fP, \fB--server\fP=""
	Node to run on (default: first node where the service is deployed)

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=10m0s
	Kill the remote command after this duration (interactive default: 4h)

.PP
\fB-t\fP, \fB--tty\fP[=false]
	Run the remote command under a pseudo-terminal (implies -i)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--events\fP=""
	stream progress events to stdout: ndjson (human output moves to stderr)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	output format: text or json (json reserves stdout for the final result document)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Inspect the environment inside the running web service
  tako exec web -- env

  # Open an interactive shell in the running container
  tako exec -it web -- sh

  # Pipe data through a command running in the container
  cat dump.sql | tako exec -i db -- psql -U app

  # Run a framework task in a fresh container from the current image
  tako exec web --oneoff -- php artisan tinker --execute='dump(1)'

  # Target a specific node and replica
  tako exec web --server node-b --replica 2 -- date
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako(1)\fP
